findings.recommendation:
Validate `next` is a relative path before redirecting. Minimum: reject anything that doesn't start with `/` and a non-`/`/`\\` second character. Replace line 20 with:

```ts
const safeNext = (next.startsWith('/') && !next.startsWith('//') && !next.startsWith('/\\'))
  ? next
  : '/dashboard';
return NextResponse.redirect(`${origin}${safeNext}`);
```

Also apply the same validation in `app/[locale]/login/page.tsx:18` and `app/[locale]/signup/page.tsx:21` where `next` is read from URL and forwarded to `redirect({href: next || '/dashboard', locale})` — even though next-intl's `redirect` likely treats `next` as a path, defense in depth keeps the validation in one place.

Add a `headers()` block to `next.config.ts`:

```ts
async headers() {
  return [{
    source: '/(.*)',
    headers: [
      { key: 'Strict-Transport-Security', value: 'max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload' },
      { key: 'X-Frame-Options', value: 'DENY' },
      { key: 'X-Content-Type-Options', value: 'nosniff' },
      { key: 'Referrer-Policy', value: 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin' },
      { key: 'Permissions-Policy', value: 'camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()' },
      // Start with report-only CSP, tighten over a week.
      { key: 'Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only', value: "default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://js.stripe.com https://app.cal.com; frame-src https://challenges.cloudflare.com https://js.stripe.com https://*.cal.com; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co https://api.stripe.com https://api.cal.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; frame-ancestors 'none';" },
    ],
  }];
}
```

The Stripe/Turnstile/Cal.com origins are the actual third-party scripts the app loads.
